Cell[TextData[{
 "In the animated graphic above we can see it seems than the wheel is \
rotating, the big circle is travelling the same distance than the smaller \
circle. But, we know that it is impossible! because the distance traveled by \
a rotating wheel is given by the expression ",
 StyleBox["d = 2 \[CenterDot]\[Pi] \[CenterDot] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["r",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", where ",
 StyleBox["r",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is the radius of the wheel. So when the radius of a wheel is smaller than \
another the distance traveled will be smaller. That is the paradox, and know, \
coding again, we will expose the explanation of what is really happening with \
the physical movement of the wheel."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7070849791504097`*^9, 3.7070850245388594`*^9}, {
  3.707085063545107*^9, 3.707085106675485*^9}, {3.7070851507339025`*^9, 
  3.70708523495259*^9}, {3.7070852789369993`*^9, 3.7070853575475206`*^9}, {
  3.707085396861774*^9, 3.707085508943366*^9}, {3.7070856109226246`*^9, 
  3.707085722377194*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8018fd02-b5c0-4a08-9a23-\
6619574734c2"]
}, Open  ]],

