Cell["\<\
After visualizing that, we can see clearly that the blue and red trajectories \
are cycloid, but the green curve is not a such kind of curve so it\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s no correspond to a pure rotating movement.
In conclusion if we force the wheel to rotate purely over the bottom line, \
the movement of the inner circle is not a pure rotating movement, it\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s must be a mixing of sliding and rotating movement along \
the top line.

Now we use the functions of WL to calculate the length of each curve:\
